Nicotine itself is very similar to caffeine in it being a stimulant, difference being that it is a(n) (more) addictive chemical. Vaping just the nicotine instead of a delivery VIA a cigarette with 8,000+ harmful chemicals from the SMOKE the cigarette itself procedures is FAR more safe, 95%+ safer. 
I have never smoked but picked up nicotine in place of caffeine to assist in my recovering from copper poisoning which came with severe physical and mental fatigue - Thanks to my lovely doctor for poisoning me. 
It has helped my mental health as well in the meantime. I have liked it more than other (addictive) prescription antidepressants. 
When the time comes you have so much control over the amount of nicotine you‚Äôre in taking to wean off effectively. 
I wish there was more talk on the evidence in the research comparing cigarettes versus  just the nicotine, a stimulant more addictive than caffeine.

title: Teen was in the fight for her life after vaping a cartridge a day I Nightline
comment:
This girl like most of those who got ill, were using ILLEGAL THC cartridges. These cartridges included vitamin E acetate, an oil which can be ingested in the stomach, but can be fatal if inhaled. She lied because of the criminal outcome (using illegal substances) and for health insurance issues (she would have to pay in full for treatment, US stupidity God bless the NHS)
All reputable vaping stores and brands have liquids which are safe to use. They contain Propylene Glycol, Vegetable Glycerine, flavouring which is highly regulated and the optional ingredient of nicotine (freebase or salt).
The vaping community does not condone underage use.
I would say if you smoke, you should vape. If you don't smoke, don't vape.
If this applies to you, you might have a local vape shop near you who can provide great help (me and my fellow vapers are a really nice and helpful bunch).
Also, only purchase from reputable brands, and do your research first.
To learn more about the effects and relative safety of vaping, you can read reports from Public Health England and the Royal College of Physicians online. 
Hope this helps.

title: Why Vaping Is Bad For You
comment:
This is perfect example of a trusted source pushing one side of an argument without considering the other. This needs an update. Recent studies have indicated that the Vaping Related Lung Injury which has lead to a handful of deaths and hospitalizations is almost exclusively associated with Vitamine E Acetate adulterated THC Liquids, the VEA is used nefariously by some to artificially pass their THC E-Liquid off as thicker (often associated with an increase in quality) than it otherwise would be. As of 2021 it has been determined that Vaping Related Lung Injury is not associated with nicotine, cbd, thc (itself), propylene glycol, or vegetable glycerin. 

The British National Health Service has OFFICIALLY endorsed Vaping w/ nicotine as being 95% less harmful than traditional tobacco products.

Science Insider has been a channel I have followed for years and I have considered quite trustworthy. I consider myself a progressive intellectual, and somewhat of a firebrand atheist who puts science and objectivity at the forefront of most considerations. In the modern age of social media, and echo chambers it is absolutely essential that sources that claim to do the same identify and update their content to reflect new information and objective peer reviewed results of recent studies and observations.

title: Why Vaping Is Bad For You
comment:
What a bullshit video. It has been known for a long time that vaping, while still unhealthy, is much less harmful than smoking cigarettes. Public Health England claims that vaping is at least 95% less harmful than smoking. 

A UK clinical trial found that smokers switching to vaping were twice as likely to remain non-smokers when compared with other nicotine replacement therapies.

If you look at the numbers in this video; 480,000 smoking deaths as opposed to 6 deaths linked to vaping, how can you then claim that vaping isn't any safer? This is some big tobacco propaganda because some people bought black market THC vape pens with harmful chemicals in them, rather than a fair comparison of smoking cigarettes vs vaping nicotine.

title: Why I'm Quitting Vaping!!! - No Nicotine November
comment:
1. Make a plan to quit and remind yourself every time you hit it how awful it is for you and what your future looks like in the hospital. This makes the quitting much easier. You‚Äôve convinced yourself it‚Äôs bad for you. 
2. Buy gum and mints. They‚Äôre 110% helpful. 
3. Don‚Äôt back out. Remind yourself that it‚Äôs weak to go back and you can push through it. 

I am on day 4. Day 1,2, and 3 were not that great, but I‚Äôm already pretty much over the cravings and had little to no physical withdrawals. I was using a ton of high strength juice on the daily so trust me, it won‚Äôt be that hard for you either. 

I had back surgery at 21 years old and my back is still awful and hurts... nicotine breaks down the discs in your back and causes deterioration of those discs. My back already feels better on day 4. I can run long distances without getting tired quick. I used to sweat a lot and that stopped. I could never go to sleep and now I have 0 trouble with it. I thought vaping was a stress reliever and found out it caused stress. I can finally hang with my family and not feel pressured to go vape. I can work all day long without craving it and cutting out every 30 minutes. 

There is zero downside to stopping. One day when people start dying from vaping, you won‚Äôt be that parent dying. Your kids won‚Äôt have to ask why‚Äôd you do that. Save yourself the money, pain, heartache, backache, headache, and seriously go for it.

comment:
Just go ahead and ban everything. I started smoking at age 12. I finally quit at age 42, after 30 years. I was never a really heavy smoker, but 30 years is a long time. While I have never smoked again, I was absolutely miserable, and it had nothing to do with nicotine. Smoking had integrated itself into every aspect of my life, and things I used to enjoy because I smoked while doing them were no longer enjoyable. Then about 10 years ago I discovered vaping. I have been doing it ever since. I DO NOT use liquid with nicotine in it. And I don't do it 24/7. But it has added a lot of enjoyment back to my life. Before I started vaping I was seriously depressed, and life had lost it's meaning. Vaping gave most of that back to me. I will never go back to smoking, but I intend to continue vaping. As part of my yearly physical a couple of months ago, I had a chest x-ray. It came back clean. No sign of lung damage. And I am having no problems breathing. I'm not saying vaping is entirely safe, in fact I don't know anything that is. I also ride motorcycles and fly ultralight aircraft. Safe? Probably not. But life is not safe. You can choose living or you can choose existing. I know many people who died at a young age and didn't do any of the things that are considered so dangerous. My brother in law, 59, just died of cancer, only 1 month after they found it. He appeared to be perfectly healthy. 

"I refuse to believe in a risk free society where the thrill of living is traded for the safety of existence." ‚Äî Nick Ienatsch

title: TOP 10 BEST VAPE MODS FOR 2021 - VAPING INSIDER
comment:
You should really do a video where you pick out the best mods "currently available" for purchase rather than the best mods for only that year.  Because there are quite a few mods that are a few years old and as such wouldn't be included in a 2021 video, but are still really good and even better than many of the new mods released.  Especially if you can save a few bucks buying an older model that are just as good, if not better than a newer model.  Such as the Innokin Proton (not the mini).  I've tried several of the newest mods this year, but I still keep coming back to the Proton because it is just an outstanding mod.  So far the only mod that's come close to beating the Proton for me is the new Aspire VROD 200, but I still prefer the Proton.  The VROD is great and even more comfortable than the Proton.  I love the plush leather grips.  But the battery life is weaker than the Proton, and while it is a good vape, I don't know what it is, but the proton just fires better than VROD.  Plus I like the battery level indicators and the screen in general on the Proton better.  And the joystick menu navigation is just hands down the best and most intuitive menu control system I've seen in any mod, period.  Right now, if Innokin came out with a new Proton that could take dual 21700's or at the very least a better battery door, I would probably buy it in a heartbeat.  My only real complaint about the Proton is I wish it was just a little bit more rugged in it's build.

And I have tried a fair few other mods.  Including the Geekvape Aegis X which virtually every site lists as it's number one mod.  Which it is a good mod, but it's battery life is pretty crap.  It's menu system is cumbersome to use.  And it's really bulky making it not ideal for travel and only good for around the house use.  Hell, I like using the Innokin Kroma R better than Aegis X.  About the only mod I liked actually using less than the Aegis X is the Aspire Dynamo, which I only got so I had a mod that could handle huge tanks (like the Valyrian 2 Pro @32mm vs the dynamo's 34mm minimum dimension) so if I knocked it over, there would be enough clearance between the bubble edge and the side of the mod, protecting the glass bubble during accidental falls.

I am really interested in trying out a Lost Vape mod though.  But man are those mods expensive.  But even so, I do really think you should do a video for the best mods currently available because there are still quite a few really good mods out there that are still better than a lot of the newest competition, but just a little older, so don't get rated in the "best of the year" videos most people tend to only get the opportunity to see.  Hell, a friend of mine recently asked me for advice of what I thought was the best kit to get and I actually recommended to him to get a Proton on it's own and buy an Odan Mini separately and gave him one of my spare Innokin Ajax tanks just in case he wanted more airflow.  After a couple weeks, he ended up calling me back to tell me the recommendations I gave him blew his old kit out of the water (which was a Smok Mag with a TFV12 Prince I think).  After he told me he wanted even more clouds and flavor, I told him to get a Valyrian 2 and use the dual coil (single coil on that tank is terrible.  Spits like crazy regardless of wattage), warned him to be careful of his smoke alarms because that thing will definitely set them off.  I've since tried the Freemax M Pro 2 Metal Edition tank and holy crap, that is the first tank I've tried that's properly giving the Valyrian 2 a hell of a run for it's money.  It's truly outstanding in both flavor and clouds.  And the coils are lot cheaper than the Valyrian 2 to where I am now seriously considering recommending Freemax M Pro 2 Metal Edition over the Valyrian 2.  It's that good and cheaper.  It's only spec that is actually lower than the Valyrian 2 is that it's max tank capacity is lower.  But when you can get just as good of a vape off it for a fraction of the cost (both in terms of tank and coils), it's kind of hard to seriously argue a little less capacity as a negative worth nitpicking.

Oh crap... I started rambling and now way off my original topic.  So I'll stop here.  Sorry for the loooong post.

I stopped for good when I started experiencing sharp pains in my lungs once a month.
But for those trying to quit, your lungs do recover.
Just prepare yourself mentally for the first month after quitting.

title: I Wish I Never Started Vaping
comment:
You should not juul or vape if you are someone who gets headaches. There are chemicals in e juices that can increase the frequency and intensity of your headaches. The chemicals that worsen headaches found in e juices are propylene glycol (PG) or sometimes vegetable glycerin (VG). These chemicals are found in I think almost all e juices. 

Too high of a dose of nicotine can also give you headaches. 

If you get headaches and are addicted to vaping I recommend you lower your nicotine dose to something like 3mg or less and switch to nicotine snus pouches like Zyn or On!. The snus does not have the chemical that causes people to get headaches from vaping. They are just pouches of nicotine I am pretty sure.

Switching to nicotine pouches is not as hard as quitting cold turkey and is helpful to anyone who sometimes gets headaches. I used to struggle with headaches and vaping only worsened them. This solution has worked for me and I get far fewer headaches now. If you struggle with migraines, triptans are also a great solution. Triptans are medicines that stop migraines and they are pretty easy to get a prescription for. Quitting vaping could possibly help you a lot in avoiding headaches and even migraines.

title: Electronic Cigarettes and Vaping
channel_title: David Geffen School of Medicine UCLA
comment: Just another hit piece. Nicotine is not a risk of great significance. The more they demonize modes of nicotine delivery that are theorized to be less harmful than cigarettes, the more people will avoid them. The difference between theories today and theories 100 years ago is that the models used today are accurate and trustworthy. We know more about the future now than we knew about the future 100 years ago. It's true we will not truly know about long term effects until 40 years from now. But we can make extremely well educated guesses, substantially more educated guesses than any educated guess that could've been made 100 years ago. Demonizing nicotine is like demonizing caffeine. It's all about grandstanding. There's no harm to any addiction that is not harmful. Addiction is harmful by definition. So if there is no harm, is it really addiction? The more government and alarmists cry from the rooftops and smear clearly vastly safer products, the more people will smoke. Humans love nicotine for the same reasons they love other drugs like caffeine and alcohol. You won't stop people from enjoying substances they like. So why smear the safest ways to consume those substances? They act as if this is big tobacco plotting against us all. But E-Cigs were invented by a smoker, not big tobacco. The lies are just outstandingly illogical...........
